    public interface IContextId
    Context identification (context id). Sole implementation of this interface is ContextId.

    Context id consists of (optional) cluster name and context name (context ids without cluster name are called cluster-less context ids). Cluster name uniquely identifies group of cooperating servers. Context names are unique within given cluster with the exception of global context which is represented by null context name value and each server has its own. When global context id has cluster name, one server from the cluster is chosen to be the one representing it.

    Non-global contexts may have additional baseline identification.

    Context id can be represented as "normalized" string with exact format: global context id is empty string, cluster-less context id is context name, global context id with cluster is slash ('/'), cluster name and slash ('/'), context id with cluster is slash ('/'), cluster name, slash ('/') and context name. Baselines are appended to context names with preceding slash ('/').

    Cluster, context and baseline names should consist only of English characters, period and hyphen/minus: .-0-9A-Za-z.

    Implementations of this class must be immutable.
